2
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:50,030
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,080
Look at my radish, so fresh.

4
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,920
These greens are super fresh too.

5
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,160
-Look at the leaves.
-They do look fresh.

6
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:56,600
Look here.

7
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,039
Look.

8
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,200
Song was right after all.

9
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,479
He really came back to life.

10
00:02:00,479 --> 00:02:01,600
How is that possible?

11
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,400
I saw it with my own eyes that day.

12
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,560
His leg was broken.

13
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,640
How could he be working here

14
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,970
like nothing happened?

15
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,680
I heard Her Ladyship went in to see him,

16
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,980
and then he just recovered.

17
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:10,680
Do you think

18
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,560
she used some method to save him?

19
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:15,560
What kind of method
could heal a broken leg

20
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,360
and bring him back from the dead?

21
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:19,960
If you ask me,
she must've used some dark arts.

22
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,600
Or maybe

23
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,680
he… he's not even human.

24
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:24,880
Not human?

25
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,190
Could he be a monster?

26
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,760
That's possible.

27
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,480
You guys,

28
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,260
if you have nothing better to do,

29
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,840
go and turn over the soil

30
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:35,910
in the back garden.

31
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:36,860
-Yes.
-Yes.

32
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,360
Yes.

33
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:40,470
Hurry.

34
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,240
Let's go.

35
00:02:48,050 --> 00:02:49,000
You are...

36
00:02:52,010 --> 00:02:53,470
Sir, when did you get here?

37
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,000
Forgive my rudeness.

38
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,370
I didn't see you.

39
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:03,140
Good, good.

40
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:19,280
I swear, this is the last time.

41
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,640
I'll never use magic

42
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,800
carelessly again.

43
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,240
You know full well that
altering a mortal's fate with magic

44
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,700
comes with consequences.

45
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,900
Why did you still save that child?

46
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,920
Hua Ruyue, we were born immortal.

47
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:41,280
We live for eternity.

48
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,600
Mortals live for just a few decades.

49
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,480
To us, that's just a blink.

50
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,480
They're no different from flowers, birds,

51
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:49,940
fish, ants, and mayflies.

52
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,400
If you see a dying ant on the road,

53
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,060
would you also stop to help it?

54
00:04:02,370 --> 00:04:03,660
I'm not heartless.

55
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,240
I just want you to take care of yourself

56
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,770
before saving anyone else.

57
00:04:09,370 --> 00:04:10,520
Got it.

58
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,440
Here.

59
00:04:18,410 --> 00:04:20,730
Next time, I really won't step in.

60
00:04:22,839 --> 00:04:24,200
Don't be mad.

61
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,000
I just coughed up a little blood.

62
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,330
With medicine, I'll be fine in no time.

63
00:04:29,050 --> 00:04:31,720
If I hadn't used a formation
to hide your spiritual energy,

64
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,980
the Heavenly Emissary would've noticed

65
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,440
and dragged you off
to the Immortal Prison.

66
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:41,720
I knew it. You're the kindest,
always looking out

67
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:42,880
for the weak.

68
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,140
You wouldn't let someone die like that.

69
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,640
It's not hot anymore.

70
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,700
Hurry and drink it.

71
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,920
But seriously,

72
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,400
